text:
It’s quite amazing that such a small place has a Chinese vegetarian stall (with vegan options) and one Indian Muslim stall with vegetarian food options, compared to those large food courts in shopping malls without any vegetarian food options.

The food here is cheap and good, those living nearby are really blessed.
A very quaint and small coffee shop. Tried the Burmese stall, and it was surprisingly good. The Nan gyi thoke ($5.5) was better than most I have tried.

You see, even thou I’m Indian. But every single time I get overcharged at Indian food stalls. Don’t ask me why, think they don’t like my face.

This is one stall run by damn honest folks. They serve up damn authentic Indian food- biryani chicken (to die for). Chutney and curry- delish.
This place got nice food but badly maintain, house fly on every table. Sad.
Nice small hawker area . wonderful nadi Berani after 10:30 am and lovely Malay food from noodles to rice dishes etc ..
